dct_alternative_sm: [Bacon's new large-scale atlas of London and suburbs : reduced from the ordnance survey, with supplementary maps, copious letterpress descriptions, and alphabetical indexes]
dct_description_sm: G. W. Bacon, F.R.G.S. 127 Strand, London.
Bar scales in furlongs and miles.
Shows streets, railroads, parks, stations, schools, religious institutions, offices, saw mills, various places of interest, buildings.
Includes parts of Vauxhall, Westminster, and Lambeth.
"For same area on 4 inch scale, see sheets 43-48."
Possibly from "Bacon's new large-scale atlas of London and suburbs..." 1894-1895.
Millbank Penitentiary shown with two gasometers and "chartered gas works."
